SIMPLE: insight
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insight
<hw>In"sight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sight
or view of the interior of anything; a deep inspection or view;
introspection; -- frequently used with <xex>into</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had an <qex>insight</qex> into almost all the secrets of
state.</q> <rj><qau>Jortin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Power of acute observation and deduction;
penetration; discernment; perception.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Quickest <qex>insight</qex>⟦br⟧
In all things that to greatest actions lead.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>insightful</ent>⟦br⟧
